She puts $100 into her 401k from every paycheck and she gets 26 paychecks so that's 100*26 = $<<100*26=26000>>26000
Her company matches her $100 by 6% so they contribute 100*0.06 = $<<100*0.06=6>>6 every paycheck
Over a year, the company contributes $6 to her 401k with every paycheck so they contribute 6*26 = $<<6*26=156>>156
Holly puts $26000 into her 401k annually and her company contributes $156 annually so she has 26000+156 = $<<26000+156=26156>>26156 in her 401k
